article.headline: N. Dakota St. 95, Mayville State 73
article.story: FARGO, N.D. (AP) -- Forward Brett Winkelman had 30 points, 13 rebounds and six assists Thursday as North Dakota State overwhelmed Mayville State 95-73. Winkelman was 8-for-12 with 21 points in the first half to help the Bison (4-3) take a 47-32 lead at halftime. The Bison closed the first half on a 30-17 run after MSU got within 17-15 on Marques Benjamin's layup with 13:46 to play. Benjamin finished with 17 points, seven assists and eight steals for the Comets (4-7). The Bison stretched their lead to 25 points with 9:02 left in the game. Guard Ben Woodside had 26 points, five rebounds and six assists for NDSU, which shot 58 percent and outrebounded the Comets 45-29. NDSU's Mike Nelson added 14 points. Tremel Gilot and Benjamin were the only Comets in double figures. Gilot led Mayville, which shot 44 percent, with 18 points.
